## Submissions
Each program in the repository should include a header comment similar to above, maintain "standard" C formatting and style, insert blank lines to separate "sections", indent statements within blocks of code, use calculations in separate statements and not embedded in `printf()`, includes comments within the code, a clear, informative, friendly user interface, ANSI C compatibility by using `int main()` and `return 0;`. Indicatively, the submission interface should make it clear with what the output represents to the user and provide example user inputs if necessary.
